name: 16-inch MacBook Pro M1 Pro 2TB 32GB
details:
"Hey there. I'm thinking of selling my 16-inch Apple MacBook Pro. This is the 2021 M1 Pro model with the 10-core GPU and 16-core GPU. It's got 2TB of storage and 32GB RAM. The MBP has been a phenomenal laptop so far, but I've been considering switching to a Mac Mini and iPad Pro when on the go. So I'm listing the machine here to see if any serious offers surface. 

I take good care of my devices, and the *only* scuff on this MacBook Pro is on the top of the lid at the right corner. I've included it in one of the photos. This blemish really isn't noticeable unless you go looking for it. Otherwise, the laptop is in phenomenal condition. The display is still scratch-free and pristine. That Liquid Retina XDR / Mini LED screen is really something else. And if you've read reviews, you know these are the best speakers you'll get on any laptop. 

This MacBook Pro is covered under AppleCare+ until April 2025. Right now it's all original hardware — no repairs have been necessary. Obviously I'll remove the stickers before handing it over to a new buyer. I'm just not going to that trouble until I've got someone lined up. 😂

The machine originally sold for $3,499, and AppleCare was another $399. Seeing as it's used, I've taken what seems like a fair amount off the asking price. Serious offers only, please, and we'll need to meet up at an Apple Store or some other safe, public location to make the exchange. I'm not interested in trades or anything like that.

You can reach me via email reply here, text, or through social media (Twitter/Instagram) at @chriswelch. Yes, I work for The Verge / Vox Media."
